Afropop singer, Kizz Daniels is jubilant as the official video of his masterpiece ‘Buga’ garnered over 10 million views in just six days after its release. The Tekno-assisted global hit jam was released on YouTube and many other streaming platforms at 4pm on June 22, 2022. The single whose audio was released on May 2 became the most shazamed song in the world barely two weeks after. “Buga” which continued to top music charts became a viral sensation with its signature dance on social media, including Tik Tok.   Inmate graduates with 2nd Class Upper from Open University     Two shot dead, 16 abducted in Kaduna     After N2.5m fine, court threatens Evans with more penalties   The massive hit which has continued to break barriers, uniting people across social classes has seen Heads of Governments in Africa and beyond jump on the dance challenge. “Buga” video, directed by TG Omori and shot on locations in Lagos and Abuja has a carnival-like setting with colourful costumes, aesthetics to entice viewers with comic acts such as Sabinus thrilling fans with funny displays. Vado, taking to the microblogging app, expressed excitement over the consistent success of his smash hit. “10million views in 6 days y’all are going innnnnnnnn I’m #BUGA”, he tweeted.